# Per-developer signing credentials (template).
#
# Copy to ios-app/env/signing.env (gitignored) and fill in. signing.env is
# sourced by bin/build-ios for any device build and by bin/install-ios for every
# install. One signing.env is shared across ALL targets, so a device build of
# any target inherits signing creds without restating them.
#
# This file is the PER-DEVELOPER / MACHINE-SPECIFIC bucket of the three-bucket
# configuration model:
#   1. Public, environment-specific (checked in, in the target file
#      ios-app/env/<target>.env): UNICOACH_DESTINATION, UNICOACH_CONFIGURATION,
#      and the optional UNICOACH_BACKEND_URL (not a secret — shareable).
#   2. Per-developer / machine-specific (local, gitignored, THIS file):
#      UNICOACH_DEVELOPMENT_TEAM and UNICOACH_DEVICE.
#   3. Actually secret (local, gitignored): UNICOACH_CLIENT_KEY. Its per-target
#      home is the future <target>.local.env seam — a gitignored
#      ios-app/env/<target>.local.env that bin/build-ios will source LAST (after
#      the target file, .env, and signing.env) so it overrides everything for
#      that one target. That seam is reserved (a comment marks the insertion
#      point in bin/build-ios) but not yet implemented; today UNICOACH_CLIENT_KEY
#      is sourced from the repo .env.

# Apple Developer Program team id (required for device builds). Find it in
# Xcode → Settings → Accounts → <your account> → the team's Team ID, or at
# developer.apple.com → Membership. A paid program membership is required for
# ~1-year provisioning profiles; free personal teams (7-day profiles) are out of
# scope. Passed to xcodebuild as DEVELOPMENT_TEAM with automatic signing.
UNICOACH_DEVELOPMENT_TEAM=ABCDE12345

# Target device UDID (optional). When set, bin/install-ios installs to exactly
# this device. When unset, bin/install-ios auto-detects via
# `xcrun devicectl list devices` and fails fast if zero or more than one device
# is connected. Find a UDID with `xcrun devicectl list devices`.
# UNICOACH_DEVICE=00000000-0000000000000000

# App Store provisioning profile NAME (optional; bin/release-ios only). When set,
# release-ios signs the App Store export MANUALLY with your local Apple
# Distribution certificate and this profile, instead of the default automatic
# (cloud-managed) signing. Use this because App Store Connect API keys cannot
# access cloud-managed distribution certificates (xcodebuild fails with a "Cloud
# signing permission error" 403). Create the profile at developer.apple.com →
# Profiles → App Store, bound to your App ID and Apple Distribution cert, then
# download and double-click to install it. QUOTE the value — profile names
# usually contain spaces and this file is sourced.
# UNICOACH_PROVISIONING_PROFILE="Unicoach App Store"
